data.oai_dc:dc: The University of Texas at El Paso Biodiversity Collections Bird material with reliable locality data is mostly from the United States, but there is also a significant component of exotic or native taxa with inadequate collection data. The collections include skeletal material along with the traditional skin-skull/study skin specimens.|Data set was developed through the work of University of Texas at El Paso faculty and students and is created to support future research.|3,077 occurrences
